    law_category: "labor",
    article_num: "87",
    text: "The regular or extraordinary termination of the employment contract must be delivered to the contracting party to whom the contract is being terminated. Delivery shall be effected in person on the employer's premises, by registered mail with acknowledgement of receipt, or by posting on a notice board accessible to the employee. The contracting party to whom the termination is delivered on the employer's premises is obliged to receive it. It shall be deemed that delivery was effected if the contracting party refuses to receive the termination. The burden of proof for delivery or refusal of delivery lies with the party terminating the contract.",
