    law_name_local: "Zakon o delovnih razmerjih (ZDR-1)",
    law_category: "labor",
    article_num: "126",
    text: "Payment for work under the employment contract consists of salary, which must always be in monetary form, and possibly other types of payment if so provided by a collective agreement. In determining salary, the employer must observe the minimum set by law or by the collective agreement directly binding on the employer. Salary consists of basic salary, performance-related pay and supplements. An integral part of salary is also payment for business performance, if agreed in a collective agreement or employment contract. For the duration of the break during the working day, the employee receives payment as if they were working.",
    text_local:
      "Plačilo za delo po pogodbi o zaposlitvi je sestavljeno iz plače, ki mora biti vedno v denarni obliki, in morebitnih drugih vrst plačil, če je tako določeno s kolektivno pogodbo. Pri plači mora delodajalec upoštevati minimum, določen z zakonom oziroma kolektivno pogodbo, ki neposredno zavezuje delodajalca.\nPlača je sestavljena iz osnovne plače, dela plače za delovno uspešnost in dodatkov. Sestavni del plače je tudi plačilo za poslovno uspešnost, če je le-to dogovorjeno s kolektivno pogodbo ali pogodbo o zaposlitvi.\nZa čas odmora med dnevnim delom prejme delavec plačilo, kot če bi delal.",
